<br>
I dunno about the &quot;more&quot; part. From what I understand (which is not very much), the typical guild gearing progression is: Kael, then HoT, then NToV...then the world is your oyster or some such thing.<br>
<br>
I can only really speak to HoT, since that is where I have spent the most time with my guild getting gear. The idea is if you go there over and over you can pretty well equip your entire guild in decent armor. Sure, my guild can kill as high Doomshade let's say (I know that is not very high, but that's where we are), but he only drops a few specific items from a limited list. <br>
<br>
The mobs in HoT have a chance to drop a quest item for any one of the 7 standard armor slots for any class on any given kill (or if you are really lucky multiple drops on one kill). By going there over and over (and then some more) you can outfit your guild in gear far beyond what most people could afford to buy/beg/borrow or steal on their own.<br>
<br>
I do not have any experience with NToV, but checking the drops from named mobs it appears there is a wide variety of pretty nice stuff that you can get off them including weapons and items for slots other than the 7 armor slots.<br>
<br>
So, it is not so much about where the best gear drops that a guild can get, but places where you can farm lots of gear for everyone in your guild.<br>
<br>
I think after NToV you move on to what? VT?<br>
